<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 07 at 10:01AM EST  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...SPOTTY LIGHT FREEZING RAIN LINGERING UNTIL MIDDAY...
Spotty light freezing rain and freezing drizzle continues across
the Southwest Piedmont of North Carolina late this morning. While
road temperatures remain fairly warm, air temperatures hovering
in the lower 30s may create light icing in spots, especially on
elevated surfaces.
Allow extra travel time and stopping distance if driving this
morning. Be especially alert for any icing conditions on bridges
and overpasses.</description>
